The accurate computation of changes in the light absorbed by vegetation under natural illumination during the day in the FOV of the instrument is a challenge. One was to consider the complex interaction between canopy structure and incident light. In addition, re-absorption of fluorescence in the radiative transfer from the leaf surface to the sensor could also play a role. However, we can approximate SIF yields by computing an apparent spectral fluorescence yield (ASFY) as:1ASFY687=F687APAR\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
